<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-04-27T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-04-27T00:00:00-05:00" n="1081" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1081">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.11/3866.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Chargé <persName type="from">O’Shaughnessy</persName>
                                to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Vera Cruz</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-04-27">
                                    <hi rend="italic">April 27, 1914</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Garden effected transit of over 40 Americans from Mexico to Vera Cruz.
                            The British cruiser <hi rend="italic">Hermione</hi> took 1241 American
                            refugees from Tampico to-day. Americans arriving from Mexico City state
                            that Carden has done utmost for our nationals. I have great fear that
                            several Americans have been injured if not killed in Mexico City.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Nelson O’Shaughnessy</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>